# .privatefiles — patterns that must NEVER be committed to the public GitHub remote.
#
# These files may exist locally on a developer's machine for AI agent context,
# debugging, or personal workflow, but their contents are not ready for public view.
#
# HOW THIS WORKS
# ──────────────
# 1. .githooks/pre-commit reads this file and blocks git commit if any staged
#    file path matches a pattern here (substring match).
# 2. scripts/setup-dev.ps1 also copies these patterns into .git/info/exclude,
#    which makes git treat them as ignored entirely (won't even show as untracked).
#
# ACTIVATE
# ────────
#   pnpm run setup:dev       ← recommended (does both layers)
#   — or manually:
#   git config core.hooksPath .githooks
#
# ADDING YOUR OWN
# ───────────────
# Add a path or pattern below. It will be picked up by both layers after
# re-running setup:dev (for the exclude layer) or immediately for the hook layer.

# ── Internal planning documents ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Not ready for public view. May exist locally for AI context.
docs/plans/next-implementation-plan.md
docs/plans/MASTER-IMPLEMENTATION-PLAN.md
docs/plans/future-backward-compatibility-plan.md
docs/plans/Architecture Plan.md
docs/plans/phases/

# ── Developer-local AI configs ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# CLAUDE.md / GEMINI.md are personal AI agent setup files.
# AGENTS.md is committed intentionally — do not add it here.
CLAUDE.md
GEMINI.md

# ── VS Code local config ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# settings.json may contain personal workspace preferences.
# mcp.json contains local MCP server paths (machine-specific).
.vscode/mcp.json
.vscode/settings.json

# ── Debug / scratch files ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
past_conversation.md

# ── Internal docs not for public view ────────────────────────────────────────
docs/Product Specs/

# ── Agent memory / progress (machine-local state) ───────────────────────────
.agent/progress.md
.agent/memory/architecture.md

